                ("rag-easy-1", "How do you design a basic text chunking and embedding pipeline for document ingestion?",
                 "### Phase 1: Conceptual Foundation & Core Architecture\n"
                 "A basic text chunking and embedding pipeline involves reading raw documents, parsing their content, "
                 "splitting the text into chunks of a designated size with a specific overlap, and passing those chunks "
                 "to an embedding model API to generate vector representations. The primary trade-off is chunk size: "
                 "larger chunks preserve context but dilute specific facts, while smaller chunks pinpoint facts but may "
                 "lose surrounding context. Typical starting values are 512 tokens with a 10% (51.2 token) overlap.\n\n"
                 "### Phase 2: Low-Level Mechanics & Implementation\n"
                 "Here is a Python implementation utilizing standard character-based sliding-window chunking:\n"
                 "```python\n"
                 "import openai\n\n"
                 "def chunk_text(text, chunk_size=500, overlap=50):\n"
                 "    chunks = []\n"
                 "    start = 0\n"
                 "    while start < len(text):\n"
                 "        end = start + chunk_size\n"
                 "        chunks.append(text[start:end])\n"
                 "        start += chunk_size - overlap\n"
                 "    return chunks\n\n"
                 "def get_embeddings(chunks, model='text-embedding-3-small'):\n"
                 "    response = openai.embeddings.create(input=chunks, model=model)\n"
                 "    return [item.embedding for item in response.data]\n"
                 "```\n\n"
                 "### Phase 3: Production Hardening & Gotchas\n"
                 "- **Rate Limiting**: OpenAI and other embedding providers enforce Rate Limits (TPM/RPM). Mitigate by using batching (e.g., 100 chunks per request) and exponential backoff retries.\n"
                 "- **Malformed text**: Filter out binary bytes, null characters, or excessively repeating control characters before embedding to avoid skewing vector coordinates."),

